--  regionArea — Boundary surface area of each region
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
--
--  For a cell-aligned boundary region A of k cells:
--
--    area(A) = 6k − 2 · |internal faces within A|
--
--  Each cube has 6 faces.  Each shared face between two
--  A-cells is internal to A and does not exit; we subtract 2
--  for each such face (once per cell sharing it).  The result
--  is the total count of faces connecting A to non-A entities
--  (neighboring cells outside A, or the patch exterior).
--
--  This is the discrete analogue of the Bekenstein–Hawking
